00:29:57,228 --> 00:30:00,198
A third party with ill intention
got a cigarette butt

502
00:30:00,265 --> 00:30:03,768
and planted it at the crime scene.
It's a possibility.

503
00:30:04,803 --> 00:30:06,504
Yes, you are right.

504
00:30:06,571 --> 00:30:07,639
In that case,

505
00:30:07,705 --> 00:30:10,809
that piece of evidence
makes no contribution as a clue.

506
00:30:10,875 --> 00:30:14,479
I can say the same about
the prosecutor's evidence too.

507
00:30:15,146 --> 00:30:18,016
The sketchbook stained with blood
found in this murder

508
00:30:18,550 --> 00:30:20,985
and the blood-stained clothes and shoes

509
00:30:21,052 --> 00:30:23,721
presented as evidence
in the murder 11 years ago

510
00:30:23,788 --> 00:30:27,926
could also be planted to put the blame
on the two defendants.

511
00:30:29,194 --> 00:30:30,261
But…

512
00:30:30,328 --> 00:30:32,463
Relying on circumstantial evidence

513
00:30:32,530 --> 00:30:34,999
to construct the image of the culprit

514
00:30:35,066 --> 00:30:37,535
is the most risky and foolish act.

515
00:30:38,136 --> 00:30:41,406
The investigation organizations
choose evidence intentionally

516
00:30:41,472 --> 00:30:44,409
and even conceal it. This is outrageous!

517
00:30:47,912 --> 00:30:49,581
