she messed up your life.

619
00:37:07,458 --> 00:37:08,659
This is ridiculous!

620
00:37:09,594 --> 00:37:12,096
This is ridiculous!
What's the point of doing this now?

621
00:37:12,830 --> 00:37:13,664
Ridiculous!

622
00:37:13,731 --> 00:37:15,399
Falsely charged of molestation.

623
00:37:16,734 --> 00:37:19,570
This is the reason that
you committed the series of murder?

624
00:37:22,607 --> 00:37:23,741
Mr. Kozu,

625
00:37:24,542 --> 00:37:26,010
I cannot forgive you.

626
00:37:28,579 --> 00:37:31,882
If you'll serve your sentence
without regretting what you did,

627
00:37:32,450 --> 00:37:34,385
I will never accept it!

628
00:37:37,154 --> 00:37:39,690
If you don't look properly
at what you had done,

629
00:37:40,358 --> 00:37:44,295
the victims and those who lost
a family member won't get closure.

630
00:37:45,296 --> 00:37:48,466
I don't care! What's wrong with you?

631
00:37:50,534 --> 00:37:52,436
Because I didn't know.

632
00:37:53,971 --> 00:37:56,440
I want to know everything about you.

633
00:37:57,642 --> 00:37:59,677
-I want to understand you.
-Shut up!

634
00:37:59,744 --> 00:38:01,612
Your Honor, I killed three people.

635
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:04,782
A serial killer who killed three women.

636
00:38:05,916 --> 00:38:08,853
I don't want that to be
all I know about you.

637
00:38:09,453 --> 00:38:10,354
Shut up!

638
00:38:11,455 --> 00:38:12,657
Kazunari Kozu.

639
00:38:12,723 --> 00:38:14,125
Shut up.

640
00:38:14,191 --> 00:38:16,827
-You were innocent 12 years ago.
-Shut up!

641
00:38:18,462 --> 00:38:20,264
Shut up!

642
00:38:20,331 --> 00:38:22,833
-You were innocent.
-Stop…

643
00:38:26,103 --> 00:38:27,672
That is exactly why…

644
00:38:29,874 --> 00:38:30,975
I am very frustrated.

645
00:38:35,379 --> 00:38:37,148
You should be the person…

646
00:38:40,217 --> 00:38:42,053
who knows the agony
of being falsely accused most.

647
00:38:51,629 --> 00:38:53,030
As a person…

648
00:38:59,236 --> 00:39:04,508
Please face the pain in your heart
until the very last moment.

649
00:39:15,152 --> 00:39:16,954
That was the case for the defense.

650
00:39:19,023 --> 00:39:21,092
Prosecutor, any cross-examination?

651
00:39:22,693 --> 00:39:23,561
No, Your Honor.

652
00:39:23,627 --> 00:39:25,062
Come on. Stand up!

653
00:39:28,466 --> 00:39:30,000
In that case, next--

654
00:39:30,067 --> 00:39:31,001
Your Honor.

655
00:39:35,840 --> 00:39:39,777
I would like to say something.

656
00:39:45,116 --> 00:39:46,117
Just now,

657
00:39:47,017 --> 00:39:48,853
the truth of a murder 11 years ago

658
00:39:49,520 --> 00:39:52,323
and these two murders have been revealed.

659
00:39:55,726 --> 00:39:59,764
I prosecuted Daisuke Asama
and claimed that he was guilty

660
00:40:01,098 --> 00:40:03,334
and drove him to his death.

661
00:40:04,101 --> 00:40:06,137
As a judicial professional,

662
00:40:06,637 --> 00:40:12,743
a decision I made
took away a person's life.

663
00:40:15,713 --> 00:40:18,983
I would like to apologize wholeheartedly.

664
00:40:28,459 --> 00:40:29,493
I've finished.

665
00:40:41,372 --> 00:40:45,109
People make mistakes.

666
00:40:46,644 --> 00:40:48,179
That's why there are criminal cases.

667
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:50,848
People are falsely charged sometimes

668
00:40:52,082 --> 00:40:53,517
and many people are hurt.

669
00:40:55,920 --> 00:41:00,458
Even so, I don't want to lose hope
in the judiciary.

670
00:41:03,994 --> 00:41:06,730
If we want to seek the truth,

671
00:41:08,866 --> 00:41:10,968
admit our mistake if we made one,

672
00:41:12,436 --> 00:41:14,705
and have the courage to correct it,

673
00:41:16,407 --> 00:41:17,475
I believe

674
00:41:18,442 --> 00:41:21,278
that we can surely
clear someone of false charges.

675
00:41:27,218 --> 00:41:28,886
The defense lawyer…

676
00:41:30,454 --> 00:41:34,124
insists that the defendant, Junpei Fujita,

677
00:41:36,961 --> 00:41:42,500
and Daisuke Asama in
Touo University Student Murder Case

678
00:41:45,069 --> 00:41:46,504
are innocent.

679
00:42:01,051 --> 00:42:01,886
It's over.

680
00:42:05,122 --> 00:42:06,056
Yes.

681
00:42:08,025 --> 00:42:09,860
But I still don't feel relieved.

682
00:42:12,730 --> 00:42:14,899
Because Ayaka and Senior Asama…

683
00:42:16,367 --> 00:42:18,202
